Sample JSON Data used to create form,
------------------------------------
form = {
        name: "TestForm",
        fields:
            [
              {type: "text", name: "firstname", label: "Name" , required: true, data:""},
              {type: "radio", name: "ide_id", label: "IDE" , options:[{id: 1, name: "Eclipse"},{id: 2, name: "IntelliJ"},{id: 3, name: "Netbeans"},{id: 4, name: "Brackets"}], required: true, data:""},
              {type: "email", name: "emailUser", label: "Email" , required: true, data:""},
              {type: "password", name: "pass", label: "Password" , minPassword: 6, required: true, data:""},
              {type: "select", name: "programmer_id", label: "Programmer" , options:[{name: "Sagun"},{name: "Ruraj"},{name: "Sushan"},{name: "Subigya"}], required: true, data:""},
              {type: "checkbox", name: "language_id", label: "Java", disabled: false, data:""},
              {type: "checkbox", name: "language_id2", label: "Scala", disabled: true, data:""},
              {type: "submit", name: "submit_button", label: "Submit"}
            ]
      }


Creating form from JSON,
-----------------------
<form name="{{form.name}}">
    <dn-input ng-repeat="field in form.fields"></dn-input>
</form>

If you use other names while iterating besides "field", you may have to manually set field attribute
e.g.
<form name="{{form.name}}">
    <dn-input ng-repeat="currentField in form.fields" field=currentField></dn-input>
</form>
